# Frontier/Mono Gasses

This page covers custom gases commonly used in Frontier/Mono atmospherics setups.

## Why They Matter
- Some custom gases are tuned for specialized power, cooling, or reaction workflows.
- They can be expensive or dangerous to produce, store, and transport.

## Handling Guidelines
- Store custom gases in dedicated, clearly labeled tanks.
- Use isolated pipe networks where possible.
- Verify temperature and pressure limits before mixing or transfer.

## Common Workflow
- Produce or acquire gas.
- Buffer in secure storage.
- Meter into your target system slowly.
- Observe output behavior and adjust incrementally.

